# API Route Handlers (`**/app/**/route.ts`)

## Security
- **Never** return API keys, tokens, or DB connection strings in JSON responses.
- Validate and **sanitize** request bodies (use **zod** or project-standard validation); reject oversized payloads when handling public forms.

## Methods
- Export only HTTP methods you intend (**GET**, **POST**, etc.); return **`405`** for unsupported verbs.

## Abuse and limits
- Public endpoints (lead capture, webhooks) should use **rate limiting** / bot protection when the project provides it (**Arcjet**, Upstash, etc.).

## CORS and caching
- If the handler is called from browsers on other origins, set **explicit CORS** policy—avoid `*` with credentials.
- Use **`revalidate`** / **`dynamic`** / **`fetchCache`** consistently with Next.js docs when applicable.

## Webhooks
- Verify **signatures** or secrets from third parties before acting; respond quickly to avoid timeouts.

## Real estate / PII
- Treat lead data as **PII**—minimize logging, align with privacy policy, and avoid echoing sensitive fields in error messages.
